gomodel:SYNGO_1029  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: The paper uses pre-embedding immunogold-Silver detection to study the subcellular localization of WLS in the fly neuromuscular junction. Wls is a multi-pass transmembrane glycoprotein essential for Wnt cell signaling.\n\nFigure 5F, 5J shows Wls/Evi at the presynaptic membrane (presynaptic compartment labelled in pink).\nFig. 5G shows Wls/Evi at large presynaptic multi-membrane structures.. Experimental description: 'Fly Strains: Flies were reared in standard Drosophila media at 25°C unless otherwise stated. (See Suppl. Materials for fly strains.) RNAi crosses and controls were performed at 29°C. The wgts flies were tested at the restrictive temperature (25°C).'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
